title: Arlo's Lullaby
description: When Arlo the Owl can't sleep, Lucas is always on hand to sing him a lullaby.

title: Extreme Bodhi
description: Lucas leads us to Bodhi the Chameleon who's all for extreme sports, dude!

title: Do You Speak Dance/A New Spider in Town/Dollhouse Mates
description: "Maizie" keeps ignoring Lucas and Findley, but not only do they learn she has a cousin, they also learn a new skill!/ Lucas befriends a bright purple toy spider, and Findley gets jealous./ Lucas and Findley move into the dollhouse together.

title: Stand Up Dimples
description: Dimples the Goldfish treats Lucas to a stand-up comedy routine.

title: Lonesome Lucas/I Can't See You/Don't Eat Me
description: Lucas wakes up in the middle of the night. How long can a night alone last?/ Lucas tries to beat Bodhi at Hide and Seek./ When Findley watches a show about spiders eating flies, he thinks Lucas wants to eat him!

title: House Flies Don't Dance/Flying the Nest/The Insult
description: Lucas and Maizie help Findley learn to dance./ Arlo believes he's a big owl now, so it's time to fly his nest. But is Arlo ready to leave his friends behind?/ When Lucas calls Findley a mean name, he tries to make things right again.

title: Flying/Dr. Lucas is in the House/Arlo's Portrait
description: After watching Findley in flight, Lucas wonders what it would be like to fly./ Dr. Lucas tries to make all his friends feel better but ends up under the weather himself./ Lucas decides to paint a portrait of Arlo. But Arlo can't sit still.

title: Jumping Pal/ Trouble at the Top/ Avocado's Fan
description: Lucas encounters a peculiar creature - A Jumping Bean. / When Findley and Avocado get shut in the attic, the stuck duo embrace the moment! / Arlo is starstruck by Avocado's popularity and becomes her biggest fan.

title: Lucas and His Friends/The Owl That Said Why/Happy Burpday
description: A series of 6 shorts introducing all of Lucas's friends and ending with a song. / Arlo keeps asking questions! Lucas learns to be more patient. / Lucas discovers a slice of cake and decides to throw a surprise party for Findley.

title: Too Hot to Handle/The Big Squeak/Big Jumping Spider
description: Findley can't resist some freshly baked cookies that are too hot to eat./ Avocado's new toy is driving everyone crazy with its noisy squeaker./ Lucas performs epic jumps all around House./ Findley is nervous and wishes Lucas wouldn't jump.

title: Sleeping Dogs/Skunked/Arlo And The Snake
description: Lucas and Findley discover a cake, and they try to keep Avocado asleep so everyone can have some./ Avocado gets skunked. Thankfully, Lucas helps her laugh at the situation./ Lucas has to convince Arlo that the garden hose isn't a snake.

title: Prickly Pals/A Sting in the Tale/Tongue Twister
description: When Arlo plays too rough, Lucas forms a new friendship with a cactus./ Maizie accidentally stings Lucas's butt. This is a shock to them both, but Maizie takes it the hardest./ When Bodhi's tongue gets hurt, it's up to Dr. Lucas to help.

title: The Mighty Boop and Fly Wonder/ Lucas and Findley get Antsy/ Mock Me Not
description: Lucas and Findley assume superhero personas, but Findley gets frustrated with being a sidekick. / The Mighty Boop and Fly Wonder find a lost baby ant. The duo is to the rescue! / Lucas playfully mimics Bodhi. But he may have offended her.

title: Sliding/Spinning Webs
description: Lucas and Findley find an ice cube. When Lucas rides the ice cube in the sink and falls down the drain, a scared Findley rallies to save him./ Lucas questions his spider-hood when he can't spin a web properly.

title: The Legend of Big Butt/ Arlo Needs a Nap/ Everyone's a Critic
description: Lucas sets off to find the legendary monster, Big Butt, who roams the garden at night. / A sleepy Arlo avoids taking a nap, worried that he'll miss out on any fun. / Lucas struggles when his web-making skills are criticized.

title: Boingo/Findley's Bad Day/You Rang
description: Lucas, Findley and Bodhi become obsessed with a new toy called Boingo./ Findley is convinced House is out to get him./ Arlo is missing his mother, so Lucas gives him a bell to ring if he needs Lucas's help - bad idea.

title: Marvelous Maizie
description: Lucas meets Maizie the Bee who's going to make the perfect landing… Some day.

title: A Song for Wimble/ I Want My Baby Acorn Back/ The Giggles
description: Findley becomes nervous when he's put in charge of taking care of House while Lucas is away./ Lucas and Findley are a little unnerved by the thunder and lightning happening outside their window. But Arlo is there to help them through it!/ Dr. Lucas is in the house when Findley says he has a cold. But is Findley being truthful?

title: I'm Taking You In/Something Up There/Home Sweet Home
description: When Arlo's mom is out, Lucas looks after him. How hard can it be?/ After hearing a screech from the fireplace, Lucas journeys up to find what is causing the noise./ Lucas and friends find a Gingerbread House and can't resist eating it.

title: Flash and Boom/ House Sitting/ Findley is Sick
description: Lucas and Findley are unnerved by the thunder and lightning. But Arlo helps them through it! / Findley is nervous about taking care of House while Lucas is away. / Findley fibs about being sick to avoid chores. Dr. Lucas isn't happy.

title: Ghost Camp/Boo/Never Boop a Robot
description: When Lucas and friends go camping, Avocado tells a scary story. Lucas now thinks there's a ghost in the garden./ Lucas loves to give his friends a scare on Halloween./ When Lucas boops a robot, he and his friends are chased around House!

title: The Altogether Song
description: Lucas sings a song about togetherness with all his friends.

title: Bye Bye Bee/Jeepers Peepers/House is Breathing
description: Saying goodbye can be hard, but there are ways to feel close to your friends./ Can Dimples finally beat Weebscuit at a staring competition?/ Lucas is convinced House is alive when the heating vent comes on.

title: Puppy Love/ House Grand Prix/ Farewell Sweet Ride
description: Avocado's friends take her on her daily walkies. / Lucas and Findley race around House to determine who is the fastest out of their element. /Bodhi processes the loss of her favorite snowboard.

title: I'll Do it in a Minute/Cloud Gazing/Don't Do That Arlo
description: Arlo has fun playing, but he procrastinates when it comes to tidying up./ Lucas, Arlo, and Findley have a day of make-believe with the clouds./ Arlo can't resist the temptation to look into next door's garden through a knothole.

title: Hey Avocado
description: Lucas rescues Avocado the puppy's kibble from her water dish.

title: Boot Castle/Avocado's Long Time Out/Tanks Giving
description: Findley discovers a boot that him and Lucas use as a castle./ When they hear Avocado has been put in her naughty crate, Lucas and Findley entertain her./ Lucas brings Dimples things from around the house so she doesn't feel left out.

title: Crack In The Tank/Big Mouth/Art From The Heart
description: When Dimples and Weebiscuit's tank leaks, they are put into new homes. They learn to accept change so long as they are together./ Dimples is worried about a tank decoration of a shark in her new aquarium. Appearances can be deceptive./ Lucas turns teacher as he tries to teach Maizie how to paint. When she thinks she's no good, Lucas encourages her to find inspiration.

title: Lucas We Have a Problem/Egg-Scuse Me/Pokey Dokey
description: Lucas helps Bodhi fulfill her dream of touching a star./ Lucas finds an egg and decides to take care of it. But he learns that responsibility is hard./ When Avocado loses her beloved toy, Lucas and Findley are determined to cheer her up.
